description: A JavaScript library for building user interfaces
author: Meta
description_long: React is a JavaScript library for building user interfaces. It lets you compose complex UIs from small and isolated pieces of code called 'components'. React has been designed from the start for gradual adoption, and you can use as little or as much React as you need.

description: A progressive JavaScript framework for building user interfaces
author: Evan You
description_long: Vue (pronounced /vjuː/, like view) is a progressive framework for building user interfaces. Unlike other monolithic frameworks, Vue is designed from the ground up to be incrementally adoptable.

author: Rich Harris
description_long: Svelte is a radical new approach to building user interfaces. It doesn't use a virtual DOM. Instead, it writes code that surgically updates the DOM when the state of your app changes.

author: Evan You
description_long: Vite is a build tool that aims to provide a faster and leaner development experience for modern web projects. It consists of two major parts: a dev server that provides rich feature enhancements over native ES modules, and a build command that bundles your code with Rollup.

author: Vercel
description_long: Next.js is a React framework that gives you building blocks to create web applications. By framework, we mean Next.js handles the tooling and configuration needed for React, and provides additional structure, features, and optimizations for your application.

author: Jarred Sumner
description_long: Bun is a fast JavaScript runtime, bundler, transpiler, and package manager — all in one. Built from scratch to serve the modern JavaScript ecosystem.

description: Build smaller, faster, and more secure desktop applications with a web frontend
author: Tauri Team
description_long: Tauri is a toolkit that helps developers create fast, secure, and lightweight desktop applications using web technologies. It leverages the OS's webview rather than bundling a full browser, resulting in significantly smaller app sizes.

author: Deno Land
description_long: Fresh is a next-gen web framework, built for speed, reliability, and simplicity. Fresh uses Deno and Preact to create fully server-rendered web applications with zero client-side JavaScript by default.

author: Nuxt.js Team
description_long: Nuxt is a free and open-source framework with an intuitive and extendable way to create type-safe, performant and production-grade full-stack web applications and websites with Vue.js.

author: Svelte Team
description_long: SvelteKit is a framework for rapidly developing robust, performant web applications using Svelte. It is built on top of Svelte and provides routing, server-side rendering, and code-splitting.

author: Builder.io
description_long: Qwik is an open-source frontend framework for building web applications that are incredibly fast, optimized for performance, and use a unique resumable architecture.

description: The all-in-one web framework designed for speed
author: Astro Team
description_long: Astro is an open-source tool for building fast, content-focused websites. Astro combines the best parts of modern frameworks with a new architecture for building content-focused websites.

description: TypeScript ORM that feels like writing SQL
author: Drizzle Team
description_long: Drizzle ORM is a TypeScript ORM for SQL databases designed with maximum type safety in mind. It is fully type-safe, supports schema migrations, and feels like writing SQL.

description: Next-generation ORM for Node.js and TypeScript
author: Prisma
description_long: Prisma is an open-source ORM that drastically simplifies database access, saves repetitive CRUD boilerplate and increases type safety. It is used in Next.js, NestJS, Remix and many other Node.js frameworks.

author: Resend Team
description_long: Resend is a developer-first email platform that makes it easy to send emails using code. It provides a simple API, analytics, and integrations with modern frameworks.
